Different primer concentrations, primer combinations, amplification temperatures, and amounts of reverse transcriptase were tested to determine the optimal RT-LAMP conditions. Optimal amplification of VHS RNA was achieved by incubation of FIP, BIP, F3, B3 primers, 8 U of Bst DNA polymerase and 1 U of AMV reverse transcriptase enzyme with the target RNA at 63 °C for 1 h. The amplification product appeared as a ladder-like pattern (many bands of different molecular weights) on the gel (Fig. 2
). There was no amplification of the negative control. The assay was able to amplify all five serotypes of VHS RNA (Fig. 2). Two additional primers, loop-F and loop-B, were subsequently added to enhance and accelerate the reaction down to 30 min (Fig. 3
). There was no difference in amplification pattern using the additional primers.
